27/04/2007
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Prime Minister Nikola Gruevski highlighted the country's commitment to NATO-related reforms Thursday (April 26th) and insisted significant progress has been made in fighting organised crime and corruption, implementing the Ohrid Framework Agreement and reforming the security sector. 
His remarks came during a meeting with representatives of a committee of the NATO Parliamentary Assembly, led by panel chairman Michael Clapham. 
(Vecer - 27/04/07; MIA, Makfax, Focus - 26/04/07)
